social_posts.post_text: The shop is back open!

Let’s talk about it in the comments mamas.
~
What are ways we can normalize/practice self-preservation over self-sacrifice?

Mothering is the most honorable & noble  service work we will ever do. 
~ 
Thank you to everyone who tapped into the conversation in our previous post in regards to Martyrdom in Motherhood. We will be diving deeper into this topic All month long. Sparking conversations that matter is our primary focus in this space right now. In hopes that we come up with solutions together and take action in our respective communities…IN REAL LIFE, beyond this app. ❤️
The joys of motherhood are abundant, but every moment is not joyful, and that’s okay.
Let this be a gentle reminder to check in on your mama friends today🖤
Mothering is both Noble and Honorable. However, we as a community are on a mission to return to our truest nature, dismissing the narrative of subjecting our worth merely to the sacrifice of self. 🖤

We appreciate when our community joins the conversation. Swipe to read a few comments from our previous post a few weeks ago about Martyrhood in Motherhood. Feel free to chime in and share how you choose self-preservation over self-sacrifice.
Take care, mama 🖤
It’s all in the work. 🖤

Hope you mamas are having a Soulful Sunday.
~
Just going to leave this thread here as a visual story of the sisterhood between the two mamas behind this brand and mission to advocate for conscious motherhood.
*
We have an ask of you today. Click the link in our profile and take 5 mins to read our “Guiding Principles”. This will give you an updated insight to the foundation we stand firm upon and what we are working towards beyond selling a product. We appreciate y’all. Take care❤️
Dear mama, Motherhood Looks Good On You 💛
Just a few wise reminders from a few wise souls 🖤
Sometimes all we have to give is a share. The rest we are savoring for ourselves. Save a piece of you for YOU, mama. With love, 🖤
How often are you reminded to rest, mama?
Whether you run a Business or Not, you are equipped to be in charge of the way you mother. That’s what we call a BOSSMOM. 🫶🏽

A few gentle reminders to save and come back to…swipe & reflect.
~
It all starts with you, mama.
~ 
Feel all the feels
~
The work we do is THE most honorable work to ever be done. This statement is not debatable.PERIOD.
~
Take care 🫶🏽

It’s official! 
~
A project we’ve been working on for some time is finally launching! 
~
Introducing Vol. 1 of our Mama Mixtape. A 5 part series featuring a mix of voices from a various mix of mamas all sharing their stories and truths through the lens of our 5 Guiding Principles.
~
Part one is live and featuring our sister-friend Jenay Hicks
speaking on the act of Sisterhood as Self-Care.
~
Link in profile for the full Episode.

I know sometimes we feel like “if not me then who”…raise your hand if you can relate 🙋🏽‍♀️
~
Make sure to check in with yourself today and if possible remove 1 thing from your list of “to-do’s” and replace it with something you NEED to do for yourself. And I mean in the most simplest way.
~
Here’s a personal example. As a homeschooling mother of 4, today instead of getting up before my children to make breakfast, I woke my teenage daughter up a bit earlier and gave her the task instead & and requested she bring me a cup of tea while I stayed in bed a bit longer to read. 
~
This small act of kindness extended from her to me, will give me extra fuel to show up for the day. Most times, we just need to ASK for more of what we need from those within reach to support.
~
Who can you ask for help today?

There’s nothing like a hug from mother to child, at any age. It’s a simple reciprocal act that feeds the soul. 🫶🏽
~
